The paper proposes a deep learning network for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The network is based on basic data processing components and is designed to be simple and efficient, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of multistage filter banks and binary hashing also suggests a potential connection to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper extensively tests the proposed network on benchmark visual data sets, indicating a focus on multimedia (cs.MM).
